                    <msItem n="6" xml:id="Wellcome_Ethiopian_16_6">
                        <locus from="283" to="292">Lines </locus>
                        <author key="">Anonymous</author>
                        <title key="" type="desc">Beginning of a prayer against devils, black Barya, Dask others</title>
                        
                        <incipit><locus>Line 283</locus>: <!-- Ge'ez text to be picked up in late-stage editing-->
                        </incipit>
                        
                        <note>According to Strelcyn, barya are a people believed to serve the demon or spirit provoking epilepsy and therefore barya is identified with this disease. Dask is the name of a devil (<ref>Strelcyn</ref>).</note>
                    </msItem>
                    
